arison of model results with paleodata from ice cores and marine sediments (1999) Journal of Geophysical Research, 104 (D13), pp. 15895-15916; Werner, M., Tegen, I., Harrison, S.P., Seasonal and interannual variability of the mineral dust cycle under present and glacial climate conditions (2002) Journal of Geophysical Research, 107 (D14), p. 4744. , doi:10.1029/2002JD002365; Qian, Z., Song, M., Li, W., Analyses on distributive variation and forecast of sand-dust storms in recent 50 years in north China (2002) Journal of Desert Research (In Chinese), 22 (2), pp. 106-111; Wang, S., Wang, J., Zhou, Z., Regional characteristics of dust events in China (2003) Acta Geographica Sinica (In Chinese), 58 (2), pp. 193-200; Zijiang, Z., Guocai, Z., Typical severe dust storms in northern China during 1954-2002 (2003) Chinese Science Bulletin, 48 (21), pp. 2366-2370; Zhang, X.Y., Gong, S.L., Zhao, T.L., Sources of Asian dust and role of climate change versus desertification in Asian dust emission (2003) Geophysical Research Letters, 30 (24), p. 2272. , doi:10.1029/2003GL018206; Yao, T., Jiao, K., Huang, C., Environmental records in ice cores and their spatial coupling features (1995) Quaternary Science (In Chinese), 15 (1), pp. 23-29; Wang, N., Yao, T., Pu, J., Variations in air temperature during the last 100 years revealed by δ18O in the Malan ice core from the Tibetan Plateau (2003) Chinese Science Bulletin, 48 (19), pp. 2134-2138; He, Q., Yang, Q., Li, H., Variations of air temperature, precipitation and sand-dust weather in Xinjiang in past 40 years (2003) Journal of Glaciology and Geocryology (In Chinese), 25 (4), pp. 423-427; Zhang, D., Anatomy of ""dust rain"" in history (1982) Chinese Science Bulletin (In Chinese), 27 (5), pp. 294-297; Yao, T., Yang, Z., Jiao, K., A study of climate and environment in the past 2000 years based on ice core (1997) Earth Science Frontiers (In Chinese), 4 (1-2), pp. 95-100; Thompson, L.G., Climatic change for the last 2000 years inferred fro